## 2. Feasibility Assessment

### Risk Matrix

| Component | Complexity | Risk | Rationale |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Domain Switcher Shell** | 🟢 Low | 🟢 Minimal | Pure navigation refactor. `navItems` → dynamic from `domainRegistry`. No existing routes change. |
| **Performance Domain (PSI)** | 🟢 Low-Medium | 🟢 Low | Single API integration. One new Next.js route handler for key hiding. Reuses existing report pipeline. |
| **Accessibility Domain** | 🟢 Very Low | 🟢 Minimal | Free from same PSI payload. Separate UI view, same data source. |
| **Security Domain Extension** | 🟡 Medium | 🟢 Low | Extends existing [SecuritySuite.tsx](file:///c:/Job/My%20Projects/Axiom/apps/web/src/components/tests/SecuritySuite.tsx) engine with URL-based checks. Pattern already proven. |
| **Visual & Responsive** | 🟡 Medium-High | 🟡 Moderate | Only domain needing genuinely new infra. Screenshot capture + pixel diffing. Serverless function or hosted API needed. |
| **Database Schema** | 🟢 Low | 🟢 Minimal | All additive — 3 new tables, no existing table modifications. |

### Architecture Compatibility

The plan's architecture aligns perfectly with your existing patterns:

1. **Zustand stores** → `useDomainStore` follows exact same pattern as [tabsStore.ts](file:///c:/Job/My%20Projects/Axiom/apps/web/src/stores/tabsStore.ts)
2. **Component structure** → New domain suites follow the same pattern as existing test suite components (config panel left, results right)
3. **Service layer** → `pageAuditService.ts` mirrors the pattern of [testEngine.ts](file:///c:/Job/My%20Projects/Axiom/apps/web/src/lib/testEngine.ts)
4. **Report pipeline** → New domains feed into existing [reportGenerator.ts](file:///c:/Job/My%20Projects/Axiom/apps/web/src/lib/reportGenerator.ts) / [reportCompare.ts](file:///c:/Job/My%20Projects/Axiom/apps/web/src/lib/reportCompare.ts) / [pdfExport.ts](file:///c:/Job/My%20Projects/Axiom/apps/web/src/lib/pdfExport.ts)
