## 4. Decisions for Your Review

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### Google PageSpeed Insights API Key
> The Performance domain requires a Google PSI API key. Do you already have one, or should I plan for the flow where we prompt the user to add it in Settings? The free tier (25k queries/day) is more than sufficient.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### Visual Testing Infrastructure
> The plan offers two options for screenshot capture:
> 1. **Hosted screenshot API** (simpler, costs money per screenshot) — e.g., screenshotone.com, browserless.io
> 2. **Self-hosted serverless** (`@sparticuz/chromium` on Vercel) — free but more complex to set up
> 
> Which approach do you prefer for the prototype? We can always migrate later.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### Domain Store Location
> The plan suggests `packages/core` for the domain store. Since mobile doesn't need domain switching right now, I'd recommend keeping it in `apps/web/src/stores/domainStore.ts` to avoid unnecessary coupling. We can extract to core later if mobile ever needs it. Agree?

> [!WARNING]
> ### `report_type` Constraint
> The existing `reports` table has a CHECK constraint limiting `report_type` to `'collection' | 'request'`. We need a migration to add new types (`'page_audit'`, `'web_security'`, `'visual_diff'`) before new domains can save reports. This is a straightforward ALTER TABLE but worth flagging.

## 5. Verification Plan

### Per-Phase Testing
- **Phase 1:** Domain switching renders correct nav items; existing API routes unaffected; sidebar collapses correctly; no visual regression on existing UI
- **Phase 2:** PSI API returns real scores for a test URL; results persist to Supabase; PDF export includes performance section
- **Phase 3:** Accessibility violations render correctly from same PSI data; WCAG checklist populates
- **Phase 4:** Web security checks run independently of API security; header analysis returns accurate results
- **Phase 5:** Screenshots captured at all 4 breakpoints; diff computation produces visual overlay; results persist to Supabase Storage

### Manual Verification
- Run the app locally after each phase and verify the domain switcher transitions smoothly
- Test on a known URL (e.g., google.com, your own site) to validate real audit data
- Verify zero regression on existing API testing functionality after each phase

