## 6. Overall Verdict

**This is a very strong plan.** The three key strengths:

1. **Leverage, not sprawl** — Three of four new domains (Performance, Accessibility, SEO) share one backend integration (PSI). Maximum surface area per engineering-hour.
2. **Additive architecture** — Zero changes to existing tables, routes, or components. The domain switcher is a navigation-layer refactor above the existing app.
3. **Honest scoping** — Visual & Responsive is explicitly capped at single-URL breakpoint diffing. Roadmap domains are "Coming Soon" tiles, not vaporware. This reads as credible.

The only domain requiring genuinely new infrastructure is Visual & Responsive (Phase 5), and the plan wisely puts it last so the audit-engine pattern is proven first.

**Ready to proceed on your approval — Phase 1 first.**
